INTENT: build a table
PHASES:
  1. create_node geo /obj table_geo
  2. create_node_chain /obj/table_geo:
     - {name: tabletop, type: box, parms: {sizex:2.0, sizey:0.1, sizez:1.2, ty:0.85}}
     - {name: leg_proto, type: box, parms: {sizex:0.1, sizey:0.8, sizez:0.1, ty:0.4}}
     - {name: leg_grid, type: grid, parms: {rows:2, cols:2, sizex:1.8, sizez:1.0}}
     - {name: leg_pts, type: attribwrangle, inputs:[leg_grid], vex:"removeprim(0, @primnum, 1);"}
     - {name: copy_legs, type: copytopoints, inputs:[leg_proto, leg_pts]}
     - {name: merge_all, type: merge, inputs:[tabletop, copy_legs]}
     - {name: OUT, type: null, inputs:[merge_all]}
  3. set_display_node /obj/table_geo/OUT
VERIFY: get_geometry_summary /obj/table_geo/OUT — expect ~600 prims
REPAIR: every chain step MUST include 'type' key, e.g. {name:tabletop, type:box, parms:{...}}

INTENT: build a chair
PHASES:
  1. create_node geo /obj chair_geo
  2. create_node_chain /obj/chair_geo:
     - {name: seat, type: box, parms: {sizex:0.5, sizey:0.05, sizez:0.5, ty:0.45}}
     - {name: backrest, type: box, parms: {sizex:0.5, sizey:0.5, sizez:0.04, ty:0.7, tz:-0.23}}
     - {name: leg_proto, type: box, parms: {sizex:0.05, sizey:0.45, sizez:0.05, ty:0.225}}
     - {name: leg_grid, type: grid, parms: {rows:2, cols:2, sizex:0.4, sizez:0.4}}
     - {name: leg_pts, type: attribwrangle, inputs:[leg_grid], vex:"removeprim(0, @primnum, 1);"}
     - {name: copy_legs, type: copytopoints, inputs:[leg_proto, leg_pts]}
     - {name: merge_all, type: merge, inputs:[seat, backrest, copy_legs]}
     - {name: OUT, type: null, inputs:[merge_all]}
  3. set_display_node /obj/chair_geo/OUT
VERIFY: get_geometry_summary /obj/chair_geo/OUT — expect geometry from all parts
REPAIR: every chain step MUST include 'type' key

INTENT: build a cup or mug
PHASES:
  1. create_node geo /obj cup_geo
  2. create_node_chain /obj/cup_geo:
     - {name: body, type: tube, parms: {cap:1, height:0.12, rad1:0.04, rad2:0.045, rows:1, cols:32}}
     - {name: handle_curve, type: circle, parms: {rad:0.025, ty:0.06, tz:0.055, rx:90}}
     - {name: handle_sweep, type: sweep, inputs:[handle_curve], parms: {crosssecttype:0}}
     - {name: merge_all, type: merge, inputs:[body, handle_sweep]}
     - {name: OUT, type: null, inputs:[merge_all]}
  3. set_display_node /obj/cup_geo/OUT
VERIFY: geometry visible in viewport
REPAIR: every chain step MUST include 'type' key

INTENT: build a lamp
PHASES:
  1. create_node geo /obj lamp_geo
  2. create_node_chain /obj/lamp_geo:
     - {name: base, type: tube, parms: {cap:1, height:0.03, rad1:0.12, rad2:0.12, rows:1, cols:32, ty:0.015}}
     - {name: pole, type: tube, parms: {cap:1, height:1.2, rad1:0.015, rad2:0.015, rows:1, cols:16, ty:0.615}}
     - {name: shade, type: tube, parms: {cap:0, height:0.25, rad1:0.18, rad2:0.08, rows:1, cols:32, ty:1.325}}
     - {name: merge_all, type: merge, inputs:[base, pole, shade]}
     - {name: OUT, type: null, inputs:[merge_all]}
  3. set_display_node /obj/lamp_geo/OUT
VERIFY: geometry visible, distinct parts present
REPAIR: every chain step MUST include 'type' key

INTENT: color geometry by Y height using VEX
TOOL: create_node attribwrangle inside SOP network
VEX:
  float minY = getbbox_min(0).y;
  float maxY = getbbox_max(0).y;
  float t = (v@P.y - minY) / (maxY - minY + 0.0001);
  v@Cd = set(t, 1.0 - t, 0.0);
PARMS: class=point, snippet=<above vex>
VERIFY: viewport shows gradient from red (top) to green (bottom)
REPAIR: if uniform colour, check runover=points (not prims)

CRITICAL: every step in a create_node_chain call MUST include a 'type' field.
WRONG (causes rollback):
  {"name": "tabletop", "parms": {"sizex": 2}}
CORRECT:
  {"name": "tabletop", "type": "box", "parms": {"sizex": 2}}
Common type strings: box, sphere, tube, grid, circle, line, torus, platonic,
  attribwrangle, pointwrangle, primsop, group, groupcombine, blast,
  merge, switch, null, copytopoints, scatter, vdbfrompolygons, convertvolume,
  pyrosolver, flipsolver, rbdpackedobject, vellumsolver
For VEX steps: {"name": "mywrangle", "type": "attribwrangle", "vex": "@P.y += 1;", "parms": {"class": 0}}
For connections: {"inputs": ["upstream_name", "second_input_name"]}
